text.paragraph:
Pediatric patients may be more susceptible to systemic toxicity from equivalent doses due to their larger skin surface to body mass ratios (see 
                              PRECAUTIONS: Pediatric Use
                           ).

Topically applied clobetasol propionate cream can be absorbed in sufficient amounts to produce systemic effects (see 
                        PRECAUTIONS
                     ).

Apply a thin layer of clobetasol propionate cream to the affected skin areas twice daily and rub in gently and completely. (See 
                        INDICATIONS AND USAGE
                     ).
